FBIS3-4825 "dreas040_h_94007" FBIS-EAS-94-040 Document Type:Daily Report 1 Mar 1994 SOUTHEAST ASIA Singapore Air Force Training Pact Signed With Bangladesh BK2702103394 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation in English 1100 GMT 26 Feb 94 BK2702103394 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Republic of Singapore Air Force [RSAF] can now train in Bangladesh. The two countries today signed a memorandum of understanding [MOU] and the implementation of long-term training. Under this, the RSAF is allowed to deploy a number of aircraft at Bangladesh Air Force bases for several months a year. Mindef [Ministry of Defense] says Singapore welcomes the move by Dhaka. It said the increased interaction between the two air forces will contribute to stronger defense ties. The MOU was signed in Singapore by the Chief of Air Force Brigadier General Bey Soo Khiang and Air Vice Marshal Altaf Hossain Chowdhury, Chief of Air Staff of the Bangladesh Air Force.
